  "myth": "Myth: In the Silence of the Steel Glades, Elara tended a fire of ancient memories. A traveler with eyes of liquid silver arrived, seeking shelter from the psychic storms. Elara offered her last spark of warmth, a fragment of her own soul, knowing its loss meant her own eventual fading. Kael, her kinsman, driven by a cold, mathematical fear, sought to extinguish the fire and cast the guest into the howling void. \"Efficiency is our only hope for survival,\" Kael hissed, raising a hammer of obsidian to shatter the hearthstone. But the blow struck only air. The traveler rose, expanding into a titan of starlight and shadow that filled the glade. \"I am the Sovereign of the Threshold,\" the entity roared, his voice the sound of grinding tectonic plates. \"The host provides the shield; the guest provides the meaning. Without the guest, the home is merely a grave.\" Kael’s flesh turned to translucent glass, condemned to stand at the perimeter, forever reflecting the faces of those he would have refused. The Edict of the Flame was born: \"To welcome the stranger is to feed the universe; to deny the guest is to extinguish the sun.\" Hospitality became the gravity that held the stars in place."
}

