  "return": 7.5,
  "myth": "Myth: In the floating Citadels of Aetheria, Elara held the Jar of Seasons, the last source of breathable air in the toxic sky. A traveler, his skin shimmering like bruised clouds and eyes like lightning, sought a single breath. To share was to shorten her own life’s span, yet Elara opened the seal, letting the fragrant breeze flow. Kael, her storm-brother, his lungs wheezing with the fear of the void, lunged to clamp the lid shut. “We cannot waste the breath of our fathers on a wandering shadow!” he shrieked, preparing to cast the guest into the abyss. The traveler didn't fall; he expanded, becoming a cyclone that held the citadel aloft. “I am the Breath of the First Dawn,” he roared, his voice the sound of a thousand hurricanes. “The host is the lung of the world; the guest is the heartbeat. To hold the breath is to suffocate the soul.” Kael was not killed, but his body became a hollow reed, forever whistling a mournful tune whenever a guest was near, unable to hold the air he tried to hoard. The Edict of the Wind was born: “To share the air is to fly; to hoard the breath is to fall.” Henceforth, the sky remained open to all who traveled."
}

